title: Bug 109350: Output parameter does not display in data set dialog
description: When calling a stored procedure from an Oracle database, the query result is supposed to be stored in an output parameter as an object. However, while in the query result page, there is no data returned and the output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
OB: While in the query result page, there is no data returned. The actual result is that the output parameter is not displayed in the edit data set dialog.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
SR: To reproduce the issue: 1. Call the stored procedure from an Oracle database. 2. Check the query result in the data set dialog. The output parameter should be visible in the dialog.
